"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756143","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost. However the Department does monitor requests we receive for new statistics and consider whether we can produce and release analysis that will helpfully inform public debate. The Department is therefore looking at this issue with a view to seeing what statistics could be produced on a regular basis.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-12T16:38:22.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756143/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756143/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Bereavement Support Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families without children aged below the school leaving age are in receipt of the bereavement support payment.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","7429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756144","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department for Transport does not hold these figures. People who are ineligible for a badge will not be asked if they have been awarded 12 points under the planning and following a journey activity of Personal Independence Payment.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-11T12:47:35.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756144/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756144/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-04","Blue Badge Scheme: Eligibility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many people are classed as ineligible for a blue badge disabled parking permit and have been awarded 12 points in the planning and following a journey activity of the personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","7430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756145","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>We are intending to publish further data on payment timeliness in due course, but our latest internal data nationally, suggests around 80% of cases are paid in full at the end of the first assessment period.</p><p> </p><p>For the remaining cases we estimate around a third have not signed up to their claimant commitment so cannot be paid until they have. The other two thirds have an outstanding verification issue, such as providing bank statements, evidence of childcare costs, or proof of rent. Many of these claimants receive a part-payment where elements of the claim have been verified.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","7328 ; 7329 ; 8923 ; 9191","2017-09-11T12:21:29.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756145/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756145/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of claimants had to wait more than 6 weeks before receiving their first payment since universal credit was introduced.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","7431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756146","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer given on 13 July 17 to question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-13/4900/" target="_blank">4900</a>.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-09-11T13:00:05.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756146/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756146/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-04","Universal Credit: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether he plans to make the universal credit helpline free of charge.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","7410"
