"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756252","Scotland Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Scotland Office Ministers travel throughout Scotland and meet with stakeholders to discuss a wide variety of issues on a regular basis. This includes the Glasgow area where I and Scotland Office Ministers have undertaken many engagements in an official capacity.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-09-11T12:51:24.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756252/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756252/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-09-04","Domestic Visits: Glasgow East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 29 June 2017 to Question 98, on which dates (a) he and (b) a Minister of his Department last attended an official engagement in Glasgow which was specifically in Glasgow East constituency.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","7642"
