"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756388","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-12","<p>The UK’s relationship with the EU's agencies upon exit will be evaluated in light of delivering the twelve objectives outlined by the Prime Minister to achieve a deep and special partnership between the UK and the EU. The UK’s future relationship with the EU's decentralised bodies after leaving the EU is a matter for the negotiations.</p><p>Prior to any decisions on establishing new agencies, the Government will, however, always look to minimise disruption and costs, which will include considering alternative options.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-09-12T15:03:11.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756388/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756388/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-04","Department for Communities and Local Government: Brexit
","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of new arms-length bodies his Department plans to establish once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756389","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-12","<p>The policy set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the National Cyber Security Strategy applies to everyone employed by the Department for Communities and Local Government, including contractors.</p><p>The Department for Communities and Local Government is committed to ensuring that contractors and their staff have a sound awareness of cyber risk matters and they take all necessary safeguards to protect the department’s information.</p><p>Cyber security awareness, the need to ensure contractual compliance with Information Assurance standards such as ISO 27001:2013 certification and “Cyber Essentials/ Plus” is included in contract specifications and reviewed as part of the evaluation process. Contractors must comply with the department’s IT security policies and procedures.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-09-12T14:38:20.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756389/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756389/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-04","Department for Communities and Local Government: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756390","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-12","<p>HMT does not have a resource board. Consultancy above £20k and less than 9 months in term is subject to Ministerial sign-off, with legal services (same thresholds) delegated to head of Treasury Legal Advisers for approval</p><p> </p><p>Any requirement above £20k and longer than 9 months is subject to wider Government and Ministerial approval as per the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/625968/20170707.__Annex_6.__Consultancy.___original_document_prior_to_changes_made_to_reflect_new_spend_request_forms_..pdf" target="_blank">controls guidance</a></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-12T10:15:23.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756390/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756390/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Treasury: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of requests for consultancy and temporary staff for his Department were approved via a resource board.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","7983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756391","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-11T16:10:51.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756391/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756391/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Treasury: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many applications his Department has received for (a) internal loans and (b) secondments from civil servants in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756392","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>Where appropriate, staff employed by the department's contractors will be subject to cyber risk management requirements as part of the contract documentation.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-11T16:08:13.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756392/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756392/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Treasury: Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the principle set out in paragraph 5.3.6 of the Government's Cyber Security Strategy that everyone who works in government has a sound awareness of cyber risk applies to members of staff employed by contractors doing work procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756393","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>HM Treasury has submitted a Strategic Asset Management Plan (SAMP) for every year since their introduction in 2015</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-11T16:09:06.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756393/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756393/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-04","Treasury: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, in which of the last 10 years his Department has submitted a strategic asset management plan to the Government Property Unit.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756394","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-07","<p>The Government is alive to the concerns around the clustering of betting shops. Since 2015, planning permission has been required for any new betting shops on the high street. In addition, the Gambling Act 2005 requires local authorities to set out in a statement of policy the principles by which they manage the gambling environment in the local area. The statement can be used to set out reasons for why it would be inconsistent with licensing objectives to grant additional licences in a given location e.g. safeguarding children or the vulnerable. The Gambling Commission advise that the use of the licensing statement of policy varies from one Local Authority to another, however where used effectively and regularly updated, they can provide an effective tool for appropriately rejecting new licenses or imposing conditions to improve safeguarding and avoid attempts at clustering.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","7899","2017-09-07T14:07:17.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756394/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/756394/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-09-04","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what information her Department holds on whether the limit of four fixed odds betting terminals per shop is being circumvented by the clustering of betting shops.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8115"
